snippet: On Day 1 of free agency in the N.F.L., Peyton Manning remained available as the music was only beginning in the league’s annual game of musical chairs.
abstract: Day 1 of NFL free agency sees Chicago Bears acquiring Pro Bowl receiver Brandon Marshall in trade with Miami Dolphins, Buffalo Bills wooing defensive standout Mario Williams and San Francisco 49ers signing wide receiver Randy Moss to one-year contract; other moves noted.

byline.original: By JUDY BATTISTA and BEN SHPIGEL

lead_paragraph: On Day 1 of free agency in the N.F.L., Peyton Manning remained available as the music was only beginning in the league’s annual game of musical chairs.

headline.seo: On Day 1, Bills Seek Williams and the Dolphins Trade Marshall
headline.main: Day 1: Bills Seek Williams as Dolphins Trade Marshall; Manning Remains Unsigned
headline.print_headline: Day 1: Bills Seek Williams as Dolphins Trade Marshall
